ourd’hui encore, d’une brûlante actualité.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  alittérature québécoise XIXe siècle, roman, Clara Chagnon, représentation des Autochtones.1 aCambron, Micheline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCambron, Micheline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChagnon, Clara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aChagnon, Clara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCôté, Sébastien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelâge, Denys, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRousseau, Guildo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9782763749938?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763749938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763749938/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles